            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are some of the most recent AI developments being reported (as of March 4, 2026), spanning policy, industry, and research:\n\n- **AI and government/defense contracting is accelerating.** One report highlights **OpenAI signing a Pentagon AI deal** for a classified, cloud-only deployment with stated “redlines,” alongside reporting that **federal agencies are moving to phase out Anthropic** over a set timeline.【6:0†source】\n\n- **Big funding + infrastructure deals continue to reshape the AI landscape.** Coverage includes claims of an **OpenAI funding round backed by Amazon and Nvidia** and a large **Meta–AMD AI infrastructure partnership** focused on GPU/compute rollout scale.【6:0†source】\n\n- **Companies are explicitly attributing layoffs to AI automation.** Reporting notes **Block cutting a large share of staff**, with the CEO citing AI tools enabling smaller teams.【6:0†source】\n\n- **AI reliability/availability is becoming a business risk.** Recent coverage describes a **major outage affecting Anthropic’s Claude**, impacting developers and businesses that depend on it.【6:2†source】\n\n- **Notable research and safety/ethics headlines:**  \n  - A study raising **ethical concerns about people using chatbots for therapy-style advice**.【6:1†source】  \n  - NASA’s **Perseverance rover completing an AI-planned drive on Mars** (AI-assisted autonomy milestone).【6:1†source】\n\nIf you tell me what you care about most (business moves, regulation, safety, research breakthroughs, or tools/products), I can filter and summarize the latest items in that lane.",
